author: Written by: FOX8Live.com Staff
title: Central City shooting leaves one man injured
text:
NEW ORLEANS, LA (WVUE) - New Orleans police are investigating a shooting in Central City that left one man injured. The incident occurred Wednesday at 4:30 p.m. in the 2000 block of South Saratoga Street.
According to police, the victim suffered a gunshot wound to the arm.
If you have any information that could help police with this case, you are asked to call Crimestoppers at 504-822-1111.
